WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.468 --> 00:00:11.488
What is that?

2
00:00:11.512 --> 00:00:14.324
Turns supers into run-of-the-mill shmucks!

3
00:00:14.348 --> 00:00:15.659
<i>You've been in a hole</i>

4
00:00:15.683 --> 00:00:18.412
ever since Ruby died.
and you've never stopped digging.

5
00:00:18.436 --> 00:00:21.164
This is your chance
to put that shovel down.

6
00:00:21.188 --> 00:00:22.165
<i>I'll have to</i>

7
00:00:22.189 --> 00:00:23.166
stick them all.

8
00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:26.503
Once they're free and clear.
it'll be my turn.

9
00:00:26.527 --> 00:00:28.338
No more sick veterans.

10
00:00:28.362 --> 00:00:30.281
no more suffering. no more Spider.

11
00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.301
What is all this?

12
00:00:33.325 --> 00:00:35.137
They're all dead?

13
00:00:35.161 --> 00:00:36.596
<i>We went to the doctor's lab.</i>

14
00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:38.515
- There was never gonna be a way out.
- You don't know that.

15
00:00:38.539 --> 00:00:41.268
I ain't gonna tell Silvermane.
But he's smart.

16
00:00:41.292 --> 00:00:43.012
He's gonna find out
what you did eventually.

17
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.261
No. not now. Come on.

18
00:00:57.850 --> 00:00:59.286
Get in! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

19
00:00:59.310 --> 00:01:00.644
<i>Let's go!</i>

20
00:01:02.271 --> 00:01:04.332
- Shouldn't we get him a doctor?
- Nah.

21
00:01:04.356 --> 00:01:05.542
He just needs to rest.

22
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:07.377
The hell is that?

23
00:01:07.401 --> 00:01:09.171
<i>Whatever it is.
it brought the big fella down.</i>

24
00:01:09.195 --> 00:01:10.714
What are we gonna do. boss?

25
00:01:10.738 --> 00:01:13.467
We are gonna find The Spider.

26
00:01:13.491 --> 00:01:15.091
- Get me Ben Reilly.
- Get me Ben Reilly.

27
00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:31.675
Look at these saps.

28
00:01:32.802 --> 00:01:34.821
Lost.

29
00:01:34.845 --> 00:01:37.306
You know.
I was like them once upon a time.

30
00:01:38.182 --> 00:01:40.494
They're blind. they don't even know it.

31
00:01:40.518 --> 00:01:44.623
Day after day. playing follow-the-leader.

32
00:01:44.647 --> 00:01:46.541
Christ. do you ever shut up?

33
00:01:46.565 --> 00:01:48.210
No.

34
00:01:48.234 --> 00:01:51.296
Why would I deny the world
a moment of my grandeur?

35
00:01:51.320 --> 00:01:53.131
Yeah. well.

36
00:01:53.155 --> 00:01:55.675
the crash is coming.
You just can't feel it yet.

37
00:01:55.699 --> 00:01:57.552
Speak for yourself.

38
00:01:57.576 --> 00:01:58.910
I'm only getting stronger.

39
00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:07.628
Times like this.

40
00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:11.090
Give me a chance to reflect.

41
00:02:11.674 --> 00:02:13.485
I don't do it much.

42
00:02:13.509 --> 00:02:16.512
Not usually
the self-congratulatory type. but...

43
00:02:17.429 --> 00:02:19.348
God. if you knew where I grew up.

44
00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:23.519
The hunger. the scarcity.

45
00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:28.148
I lost two brothers
before I was even born.

46
00:02:30.109 --> 00:02:32.027
It was madness. what I experienced.

47
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:37.884
Do you know the difference between me
and the countless other degenerates

48
00:02:37.908 --> 00:02:39.243
that came out of that time?

49
00:02:40.327 --> 00:02:43.098
A gambler's heart. simple as that.

50
00:02:43.122 --> 00:02:45.809
It's not strength...

51
00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:48.377
or guile or ruthlessness.

52
00:02:49.879 --> 00:02:51.046
It's just courage.

53
00:02:55.217 --> 00:02:56.820
And restlessness.

54
00:02:56.844 --> 00:02:58.488
It was never enough.

55
00:02:58.512 --> 00:02:59.739
I could never stop.

56
00:02:59.763 --> 00:03:01.765
never get comfortable.

57
00:03:07.438 --> 00:03:09.440
That's my advice to you.

58
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:15.714
"Never get comfortable"?

59
00:03:15.738 --> 00:03:18.300
Never be satisfied.

60
00:03:18.324 --> 00:03:19.759
Don't accept what you're given.

61
00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:22.470
Because nobody's going
to give you what you want.

62
00:03:22.494 --> 00:03:25.623
They're going to give you what they want
to give you for their own reasons.

63
00:03:31.921 --> 00:03:33.648
That's enough of that.

64
00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:35.215
Story time's over.

65
00:03:37.134 --> 00:03:38.802
Need to take a leak.

66
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:01.909
It's Cat. I need to see you.

67
00:04:17.299 --> 00:04:19.527
Thank God.
I was worried you weren't going to.

68
00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:22.346
That's for Ben.

69
00:04:23.180 --> 00:04:25.158
I deserved that.

70
00:04:25.182 --> 00:04:27.184
And that's for me.

71
00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:30.789
Ben put everything on the line for you.

72
00:04:30.813 --> 00:04:32.624
and you used that to betray him.

73
00:04:32.648 --> 00:04:35.293
That doctor cut him to pieces.

74
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:36.586
I swear I didn't know

75
00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:38.004
she was going to hurt him.

76
00:04:38.028 --> 00:04:40.215
I thought it was for the best.

77
00:04:40.239 --> 00:04:43.074
Ben told me himself
he didn't want to be The...

78
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:46.870
So now you care
about keeping his secret?

79
00:04:47.663 --> 00:04:51.500
Telling Faber
about Ben wasn't your call to make.

80
00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:53.895
I can make it up to him.

81
00:04:53.919 --> 00:04:55.063
That's rich. honey.

82
00:04:55.087 --> 00:04:56.690
No. I promise. You just have to trust me.

83
00:04:56.714 --> 00:04:58.274
Yeah. I already tried that.

84
00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:00.235
You're a liar.

85
00:05:00.259 --> 00:05:01.611
A manipulator.

86
00:05:01.635 --> 00:05:03.029
I did it for love.

87
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:04.304
For whose love?

88
00:05:05.389 --> 00:05:06.723
Flint.

89
00:05:12.396 --> 00:05:14.398
But Ben is a good man.

90
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:17.943
I promise I can make it up to him.

91
00:05:19.319 --> 00:05:20.571
How?

92
00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:24.783
If he gives me the antidote.
I can inject Flint and Dirk with it.

93
00:05:25.868 --> 00:05:28.454
I can get close to them
without causing any suspicion.

94
00:05:29.538 --> 00:05:31.057
And it's not your choice to make.

95
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:32.833
Ben can decide for himself.

96
00:05:38.714 --> 00:05:40.608
You know. I've been thinking.

97
00:05:40.632 --> 00:05:41.943
Who asked you to?

98
00:05:41.967 --> 00:05:43.886
See. that there's the problem.

99
00:05:45.054 --> 00:05:47.991
Why are we running errands
for this old man

100
00:05:48.015 --> 00:05:50.118
when we're the ones with all the powers?

101
00:05:50.142 --> 00:05:52.203
What do we need him for?

102
00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:54.330
I suppose you don't believe in loyalty.

103
00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:57.250
Loyalty. Loyalty.

104
00:05:57.274 --> 00:05:59.085
What you call "loyalty."

105
00:05:59.109 --> 00:06:00.819
I call "manipulation."

106
00:06:02.196 --> 00:06:05.032
What does serving Silvermane get us
versus what it gets him?

107
00:06:07.618 --> 00:06:09.429
How loyal would he be to you

108
00:06:09.453 --> 00:06:12.265
if you didn't follow his orders?

109
00:06:12.289 --> 00:06:14.976
You know what? Don't answer that.

110
00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:16.936
We'll just ask your old pal Winston.

111
00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:19.004
Wait. We can't. He's dead.

112
00:06:23.467 --> 00:06:24.819
Isn't that his secretary?

113
00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:26.154
Yeah.

114
00:06:26.178 --> 00:06:28.054
She's nice.

115
00:06:38.524 --> 00:06:40.752
Where ya been?
Peoples been looking all over for ya.

116
00:06:40.776 --> 00:06:42.545
People have been.

117
00:06:42.569 --> 00:06:44.839
And which people. specifically?

118
00:06:44.863 --> 00:06:46.466
Robbie people for starters.

119
00:06:46.490 --> 00:06:47.884
Ben's over at his place.

120
00:06:47.908 --> 00:06:51.096
Robbie says
he've been run through the ringer.

121
00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:54.224
He has been. He... has... been.

122
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:56.184
- What?
- Has.

123
00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:57.751
Make up your damn mind.

124
00:07:02.506 --> 00:07:03.858
Reilly Investigation <i>- Janet. honey.</i>

125
00:07:03.882 --> 00:07:05.235
Hey. Hank.

126
00:07:05.259 --> 00:07:08.446
Didn't hear it from me. but your boss.
Reilly. is in hot. hot water.

127
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:09.948
<i>I don't know what he done.</i>

128
00:07:09.972 --> 00:07:11.908
but every precinct
in the city's looking for the guy.

129
00:07:11.932 --> 00:07:13.409
<i>That's coming straight from the mayor.</i>

130
00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:15.245
<i>You watch yourself. honey.</i>

131
00:07:15.269 --> 00:07:17.330
Thank you. Hank.

132
00:07:17.354 --> 00:07:19.481
Stop it. And stay.

133
00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:33.513
Now. if I was giving stage direction.

134
00:07:33.537 --> 00:07:36.933
I'd call that. "In a rush to meet someone."

135
00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:38.374
Yeah.

136
00:07:50.262 --> 00:07:52.574
- How's the patient?
- Alive.

137
00:07:52.598 --> 00:07:54.492
But he still doesn't have his powers back.

138
00:07:54.516 --> 00:07:55.910
He needs more rest.

139
00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:57.644
You still look like a banana.

140
00:07:58.729 --> 00:08:00.039
An overripe banana.

141
00:08:00.063 --> 00:08:01.416
Those bruises are really settling in.

142
00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.317
Yeah. sure.

143
00:08:04.443 --> 00:08:05.670
How do you feel?

144
00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:07.172
Worse than I look.

145
00:08:07.196 --> 00:08:08.339
How's the other guy?

146
00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:09.591
On his way to Niagara Falls

147
00:08:09.615 --> 00:08:10.866
with his mother.

148
00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:14.953
Listen. I have to tell you something.

149
00:08:15.954 --> 00:08:19.392
- Cat asked me to meet her.
- What? When?

150
00:08:19.416 --> 00:08:22.770
This evening. She wants you to give her
the antidote so she can inject Flint

151
00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.063
and the other one Leyden.

152
00:08:24.087 --> 00:08:26.524
She said she can get close enough.
and they wouldn't see it coming.

153
00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:28.193
Fool me once.

154
00:08:28.217 --> 00:08:29.593
I don't know.

155
00:08:30.427 --> 00:08:32.197
It's not such a bad idea.

156
00:08:32.221 --> 00:08:33.823
How many times did Lonnie hit you
in the head?

157
00:08:33.847 --> 00:08:35.325
The woman just finished betraying you.

158
00:08:35.349 --> 00:08:36.784
And why do you think she did?

159
00:08:36.808 --> 00:08:37.869
For Flint.

160
00:08:37.893 --> 00:08:40.496
- She told me herself.
- That's right. She wants to save Flint.

161
00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:43.272
If she believes this'll help her.
you can bet she'll do it.

162
00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:48.379
- Who is it?
- Little pigs.

163
00:08:48.403 --> 00:08:50.340
- little pigs...
- Leyden.

164
00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:52.383
- Let me in.
- What's he doing here?

165
00:08:52.407 --> 00:08:56.095
Or I'll huff. and I'll. puff.

166
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:58.372
And I'll blow your house down.

167
00:08:59.373 --> 00:09:01.226
Thank you. Thank you.

168
00:09:01.250 --> 00:09:03.252
Thank you.

169
00:09:07.339 --> 00:09:09.525
- You look like shit.
- What of it?

170
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:11.736
Yeah. what of it? Tell that to Gielgud.

171
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:14.470
Guy said I got the chin
like a donkey's asshole.

172
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:19.911
Why do I feel like I've met you before?

173
00:09:19.935 --> 00:09:23.248
Because we have. a few nights ago.
at Silvermane's penthouse.

174
00:09:23.272 --> 00:09:24.999
I sang you the acting song.

175
00:09:25.023 --> 00:09:26.334
What's the matter? You didn't like it?

176
00:09:26.358 --> 00:09:29.254
No. no. no. no. I mean. before that.

177
00:09:29.278 --> 00:09:31.256
Maybe you slept with the wrong guy's wife.

178
00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:33.675
So what the hell

179
00:09:33.699 --> 00:09:34.842
happened to you?

180
00:09:34.866 --> 00:09:36.928
I took pictures
of the right woman's husband.

181
00:09:36.952 --> 00:09:38.996
What do you want?

182
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:42.350
Him. On your feet.

183
00:09:42.374 --> 00:09:44.084
The boss wants to talk to you.

184
00:09:45.127 --> 00:09:47.689
"Talk to me" talk to me?
Or just talk to me?

185
00:09:47.713 --> 00:09:50.733
I want to know what kind of goodbye
I should give my friends.

186
00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:52.193
I don't think you need to divvy up your

187
00:09:52.217 --> 00:09:53.945
three worldly possessions just yet.

188
00:09:53.969 --> 00:09:55.220
Now get up.

189
00:09:58.807 --> 00:10:00.410
All right. I'm coming.

190
00:10:00.434 --> 00:10:03.603
I'm coming.
Just want to grab my coat first.

191
00:10:12.487 --> 00:10:14.905
Don't worry.
We'll keep ya nice and toasty.

192
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:07.703
Hey. Reilly.

193
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:09.438
are you listening to me?

194
00:12:10.397 --> 00:12:13.418
The thing is... you could have just asked.

195
00:12:13.442 --> 00:12:14.710
I thought we were friends.

196
00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:16.212
Course we are.

197
00:12:16.236 --> 00:12:19.382
but it was a matter of some urgency.

198
00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:23.719
I can't have your friend running around
the city neutralizing my advantages.

199
00:12:23.743 --> 00:12:28.039
So I'll kindly ask you to lift the phone
and call your Spider-friend.

200
00:12:38.633 --> 00:12:40.403
Nah. I don't think I will.

201
00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:41.863
Excuse me?

202
00:12:41.887 --> 00:12:44.198
I'm not in the mood to talk to The Spider.

203
00:12:44.222 --> 00:12:46.451
The truth is. he's kind of hard to talk to.

204
00:12:46.475 --> 00:12:47.869
especially on the phone.

205
00:12:47.893 --> 00:12:51.104
Hey. buddy. can you remove the mask
so a guy can actually hear?

206
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.041
Is this some kind of joke?

207
00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:55.793
A piece of humor I'm not grasping?

208
00:12:55.817 --> 00:12:58.463
No. I mean it.
I genuinely can't understand

209
00:12:58.487 --> 00:13:00.298
half of what comes out of his mouth.

210
00:13:00.322 --> 00:13:03.050
Well. you've seen him.
He wears a stupid sock on his head.

211
00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.636
I told you when we first met

212
00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:07.787
that your mouth might
get you killed one day.

213
00:13:09.748 --> 00:13:12.018
Today might just be that day.

214
00:13:12.042 --> 00:13:14.103
Nah. You need me.

215
00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.605
This is a negotiation.

216
00:13:15.629 --> 00:13:18.608
You need The Spider.
Ipso facto. you need me.

217
00:13:18.632 --> 00:13:21.194
Res ipso locutor.

218
00:13:21.218 --> 00:13:22.578
Well. I mean. I don't speak Latin.

219
00:13:23.386 --> 00:13:26.616
Besides. word on the street is
Mayor Morris is interested

220
00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:28.493
in Señor Spider. as well.

221
00:13:28.517 --> 00:13:31.078
So. gee-whiz. deep pockets on all sides.

222
00:13:31.102 --> 00:13:34.189
What's a down-on-his-luck
private investigator to do?

223
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:41.672
Okay. then. $500.

224
00:13:41.696 --> 00:13:44.300
The number
I'm thinking of starts with a five.

225
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:45.824
but it don't end with a hundred.

226
00:13:47.118 --> 00:13:49.722
Careful. my friend.

227
00:13:49.746 --> 00:13:53.142
You want me to pay you. but you want
to continue living after the fact?

228
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:54.435
And that's exactly right.

229
00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:56.979
I want to live. as in live-live.
and that costs money.

230
00:13:57.003 --> 00:13:59.232
At first I was thinking. Santorini.

231
00:13:59.256 --> 00:14:01.359
but. no. now I'm thinking France.

232
00:14:01.383 --> 00:14:03.778
Feels romantic and safe.

233
00:14:03.802 --> 00:14:05.613
Even for a guy with a mouth like mine.

234
00:14:05.637 --> 00:14:06.989
A thousand.

235
00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:08.991
You wouldn't even miss it if I said ten.

236
00:14:09.015 --> 00:14:10.451
It's the principle. fella.

237
00:14:10.475 --> 00:14:12.161
Like you say. we're negotiating.

238
00:14:12.185 --> 00:14:13.663
- Three.
- Two.

239
00:14:13.687 --> 00:14:14.956
Deal.

240
00:14:14.980 --> 00:14:17.083
Okay. Now that that's settled. Cat.

241
00:14:17.107 --> 00:14:19.544
be a diamond and pour Mr. Byrne
and myself a glass of

242
00:14:19.568 --> 00:14:21.128
the. Green Spot.

243
00:14:21.152 --> 00:14:22.862
Get this man a telephone.

244
00:14:29.327 --> 00:14:30.471
I would have done it for one.

245
00:14:30.495 --> 00:14:32.538
Would have happily paid you ten.

246
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:37.876
It's ringing.

247
00:14:38.587 --> 00:14:39.647
Yeah. hi. It's Ben.

248
00:14:39.671 --> 00:14:42.733
Yeah. I know. I know.
I'm sorry to call so late. I.

249
00:14:42.757 --> 00:14:44.068
What?

250
00:14:44.092 --> 00:14:46.237
You did what?

251
00:14:46.261 --> 00:14:47.905
That's fantastic.

252
00:14:47.929 --> 00:14:50.074
Okay. well. listen.
I'm here with Silvermane.

253
00:14:50.098 --> 00:14:52.326
Tell him no hard feelings
about the other day.

254
00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:54.328
Bygones should be allowed
to be themselves.

255
00:14:54.352 --> 00:14:56.789
- Tell him.
- He says he wants you to know

256
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:59.417
that there are no hard feelings
about the other day.

257
00:14:59.441 --> 00:15:00.710
Tell him the bygone thing.

258
00:15:00.734 --> 00:15:03.921
And that bygones should be allowed
to be...

259
00:15:03.945 --> 00:15:05.256
something. and I.

260
00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:07.341
Tell him I just want to have a little chat.

261
00:15:07.365 --> 00:15:08.676
He just wants to have a little chat.

262
00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:10.951
- Tell him.
- You know what? Tell him yourself.

263
00:15:15.749 --> 00:15:17.958
Mr. Spider. sir.

264
00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:23.733
Well. that is something to consider.

265
00:15:23.757 --> 00:15:27.302
in regard to. all heretofore
relevant ascertained information.

266
00:15:28.303 --> 00:15:30.531
Why the hell are you talking like that?

267
00:15:30.555 --> 00:15:32.348
I'm doing Ben.

268
00:15:34.392 --> 00:15:36.704
The life of Ben Reilly. and what else?

269
00:15:36.728 --> 00:15:40.272
I-I don't want you to overestimate
the importance of that relationship.

270
00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:47.757
Okay. fair enough.

271
00:15:47.781 --> 00:15:49.240
I'll be there.

272
00:15:51.284 --> 00:15:52.637
What?

273
00:15:52.661 --> 00:15:54.120
He wants the antidote.

274
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:57.874
But he wants The Spider
to bring it to him.

275
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.811
- He's on his way.
- Great. And now. sir.

276
00:16:00.835 --> 00:16:02.855
if you don't mind. I'll take my two Gs.

277
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:05.691
Or. as they say in France.
I'll have my Cecil B.

278
00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:06.942
Deux Mille.

279
00:16:06.966 --> 00:16:08.110
Good one.

280
00:16:08.134 --> 00:16:11.322
but the money was for delivery
of The Spider. and not for the phone call.

281
00:16:11.346 --> 00:16:14.825
All right. well. in that case.
how about another round?

282
00:16:14.849 --> 00:16:17.828
What else you got back there
that normal people can't afford?

283
00:16:17.852 --> 00:16:19.455
How about something American this time?

284
00:16:19.479 --> 00:16:22.375
Maybe some bourbon.
or is that not fancy enough for you?

285
00:16:22.399 --> 00:16:24.335
Three to one The Spider doesn't show.

286
00:16:24.359 --> 00:16:26.045
He'd be wise not to. that's for sure.

287
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:27.880
Why do you want The Spider anyway?

288
00:16:27.904 --> 00:16:29.507
He's kind of over the hill. don't you think?

289
00:16:29.531 --> 00:16:30.758
I don't know what makes you say that.

290
00:16:30.782 --> 00:16:32.885
I think he looks remarkably fit.

291
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:35.536
Besides. he handled
that soft clown. no problem.

292
00:16:36.913 --> 00:16:41.227
Tell us. Do you think The Spider would
have any interest in working for me?

293
00:16:41.251 --> 00:16:44.271
I wouldn't hold it against him
that he backed the wrong horse.

294
00:16:44.295 --> 00:16:46.440
I haven't the faintest idea.

295
00:16:46.464 --> 00:16:48.651
The Spider tends to do
what The Spider wants to do.

296
00:16:48.675 --> 00:16:50.861
He's actually extremely annoying.

297
00:16:50.885 --> 00:16:51.928
Yeah.

298
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.198
What the hell is going on?

299
00:16:54.222 --> 00:16:56.158
I'm earning myself some traveling money.

300
00:16:56.182 --> 00:16:58.661
I'd invite you to join me.
but we know how that goes.

301
00:16:58.685 --> 00:17:01.497
And I could've told Silvermane
that you're The Spider.

302
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:03.457
And I could've told him you're his rat.

303
00:17:03.481 --> 00:17:05.209
I still can.

304
00:17:05.233 --> 00:17:07.151
Guess we've got each other
by the throats. then.

305
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:11.424
When The Spider comes.

306
00:17:11.448 --> 00:17:14.159
the two of you are not
to make a move until I say so.

307
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.287
I swear I've met that guy somewhere.

308
00:17:18.288 --> 00:17:19.557
Pay attention.

309
00:17:19.581 --> 00:17:22.041
Nothing happens until I give the go-ahead.

310
00:17:23.042 --> 00:17:24.687
Understood?

311
00:17:24.711 --> 00:17:27.606
Aye-aye. <i>mon capitaine.</i>

312
00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:29.316
So. are you gonna give me the antidote?

313
00:17:29.340 --> 00:17:31.694
You're the perfect distraction.
I can do it right now.

314
00:17:31.718 --> 00:17:34.280
Funny thing is. I believe you.
but I don't have it.

315
00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:35.573
Are you serious?

316
00:17:35.597 --> 00:17:37.037
What are you two yammering on about?

317
00:17:37.974 --> 00:17:41.203
I was just telling Cat about
the French island where I intend

318
00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:43.456
to spend the traveling money
you're about to pay me.

319
00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:46.083
Beautiful sandy beaches.

320
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:49.503
lush valleys. hilltop villages.

321
00:17:49.527 --> 00:17:53.299
- Sounds dull.
- Agreed. Perfect place to be alone.

322
00:17:53.323 --> 00:17:54.615
- Cheers.
- Good luck.

323
00:17:56.409 --> 00:17:58.679
That's where I know you from.

324
00:17:58.703 --> 00:18:00.181
France.

325
00:18:00.205 --> 00:18:02.641
I don't have a clue
what you're talking about. buddy.

326
00:18:02.665 --> 00:18:04.769
and I'm a detective. so buzz off.

327
00:18:04.793 --> 00:18:07.521
No. no. no. I'm certain of it.

328
00:18:07.545 --> 00:18:09.398
Meuse-Argonne.

329
00:18:09.422 --> 00:18:12.818
You're the fellow that saved us
from that POW camp.

330
00:18:12.842 --> 00:18:14.135
Hold on.

331
00:18:14.719 --> 00:18:16.280
You two know each other?

332
00:18:16.304 --> 00:18:18.616
Yeah. Flint knows him. too.

333
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:21.368
You guys are drunk.

334
00:18:21.392 --> 00:18:23.078
Never touched a drop in my life.

335
00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:24.663
Let me get this straight.

336
00:18:24.687 --> 00:18:29.376
Our private detective friend here was
in the same POW camp as the two of you?

337
00:18:29.400 --> 00:18:31.611
- Lonnie. too.
- And Addison.

338
00:18:33.279 --> 00:18:35.674
In other words. this man

339
00:18:35.698 --> 00:18:38.969
was at the site where all of you
got experimented on?

340
00:18:38.993 --> 00:18:40.930
And this very same man

341
00:18:40.954 --> 00:18:43.205
just happens to be best friends
with The Spider?

342
00:18:44.916 --> 00:18:46.352
I think The Spider hasn't walked

343
00:18:46.376 --> 00:18:50.254
through that door yet because he's already
sitting right here at my table.

344
00:18:55.510 --> 00:18:58.113
You guys are grasping at straws.

345
00:18:58.137 --> 00:19:01.933
The reason why I'm chummy
with Le Spider is because...

346
00:19:05.353 --> 00:19:06.914
because I...

347
00:19:06.938 --> 00:19:09.542
I saved his ass at Meuse-Argonne.

348
00:19:09.566 --> 00:19:12.795
Yeah. that's right.
I mean. this isn't some grand conspiracy.

349
00:19:12.819 --> 00:19:14.278
Is that so?

350
00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:16.990
It is so.

351
00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:23.806
What is this? A parlor trick?

352
00:19:23.830 --> 00:19:26.475
You're gonna focus your mind.
stick your finger in your ear

353
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:27.977
and peer into my soul?

354
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:30.896
No. I don't think
we'll be needing any magic.

355
00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:32.982
Save that for
the children's birthday parties.

356
00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:35.609
Well. then. what? You want to check
my pockets for unmarked bills?

357
00:19:35.633 --> 00:19:38.112
Here. I'll make it easy for you. I've got...

358
00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:40.030
a nickel. and...

359
00:19:40.054 --> 00:19:44.451
Not one but count 'em two sticks of gum.

360
00:19:44.475 --> 00:19:46.829
Jesus.

361
00:19:46.853 --> 00:19:48.706
You're a cool customer.

362
00:19:48.730 --> 00:19:50.291
But here's the thing.

363
00:19:50.315 --> 00:19:51.959
I'm a bit like you.

364
00:19:51.983 --> 00:19:53.377
A detective.

365
00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:55.921
I watch. I listen.

366
00:19:55.945 --> 00:19:58.323
I keep track of things. up here.

367
00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:01.910
Another drink. would you. dear?

368
00:20:02.911 --> 00:20:03.953
Absolutely.

369
00:20:08.833 --> 00:20:10.728
And just like you.

370
00:20:10.752 --> 00:20:14.899
the only person
that I am truly loyal to is me.

371
00:20:14.923 --> 00:20:19.153
So. if I know a way to find out decisively

372
00:20:19.177 --> 00:20:21.947
whether or not you. Ben Reilly.
are The Spider.

373
00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:24.158
I'll do it no matter the consequences.

374
00:20:24.182 --> 00:20:25.868
Do you understand what I'm saying?

375
00:20:25.892 --> 00:20:27.518
I can't say that I do.

376
00:20:28.144 --> 00:20:29.561
Sit.

377
00:20:31.522 --> 00:20:33.959
Now. here's how I see it.

378
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:39.465
Ben Reilly is a private dick who doesn't
care about anyone else except himself.

379
00:20:39.489 --> 00:20:42.801
But the one thing I know
about The Spider is he cares.

380
00:20:42.825 --> 00:20:45.512
He's never been passive
about innocent deaths.

381
00:20:45.536 --> 00:20:46.931
Not on his watch.

382
00:20:46.955 --> 00:20:49.350
Not if there's anything he can do about it.

383
00:20:49.374 --> 00:20:50.601
I wouldn't know.

384
00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:52.227
I would.

385
00:20:52.251 --> 00:20:53.461
Give us your gun.

386
00:20:56.047 --> 00:20:58.591
The one you think nobody knows about.

387
00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:01.487
So...

388
00:21:01.511 --> 00:21:03.656
I'm convinced.

389
00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:05.449
but I'm not certain.

390
00:21:05.473 --> 00:21:08.994
Sure. I'm convinced
we're all gonna die. but...

391
00:21:09.018 --> 00:21:10.704
there's only one way to be certain.

392
00:21:10.728 --> 00:21:13.272
Yeah. Exactly. You're quite clever.

393
00:21:14.107 --> 00:21:18.295
Now. I look around this room
and I see a bunch of tough elements.

394
00:21:18.319 --> 00:21:20.631
Gangsters. mobsters.

395
00:21:20.655 --> 00:21:22.216
hardened criminals.

396
00:21:22.240 --> 00:21:25.344
Not exactly the type that The Spider
would lose any sleep over.

397
00:21:25.368 --> 00:21:26.512
Right?

398
00:21:26.536 --> 00:21:28.222
But there's one exception.

399
00:21:28.246 --> 00:21:31.058
One innocent bystander.

400
00:21:31.082 --> 00:21:33.852
One person that The Spider
simply could not

401
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:35.795
sit back and allow to die.

402
00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:38.691
Cut it out. I'm not in the mood.

403
00:21:38.715 --> 00:21:40.442
Well. I wouldn't think you would be.

404
00:21:40.466 --> 00:21:42.277
I mean it. It's not funny.

405
00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:43.553
Far from it.

406
00:21:44.303 --> 00:21:45.930
It's tragic if we lose you.

407
00:21:46.931 --> 00:21:49.517
Bad for business. bad for my heart.

408
00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:52.270
You know how much you bring me joy.

409
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:54.439
But the way I see it...

410
00:21:56.107 --> 00:21:58.276
this is the only way that I can be certain.

411
00:21:59.527 --> 00:22:01.714
Let go of me. Finn. Now!

412
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:04.008
My God.

413
00:22:04.032 --> 00:22:06.260
It's the best damn show in town.

414
00:22:06.284 --> 00:22:07.344
So...

415
00:22:07.368 --> 00:22:09.221
if I kill her.

416
00:22:09.245 --> 00:22:11.890
then you're just Ben Reilly.
a clever private investigator

417
00:22:11.914 --> 00:22:13.851
who doesn't care about
anybody but himself.

418
00:22:13.875 --> 00:22:16.687
or you really are The Spider.

419
00:22:16.711 --> 00:22:19.213
and you'll stop me
before I pull this trigger.

420
00:22:25.845 --> 00:22:27.656
Listen.

421
00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:30.075
He's not going to save me.

422
00:22:30.099 --> 00:22:32.077
but not because he's a bad man.

423
00:22:32.101 --> 00:22:33.394
So. why. then?

424
00:22:34.187 --> 00:22:36.939
It's okay. dear. Absolution awaits.

425
00:22:38.775 --> 00:22:40.192
Because I broke his heart.

426
00:22:43.988 --> 00:22:46.365
- Why'd you do that?
- You know why.

427
00:22:48.117 --> 00:22:49.911
I want to hear you say it.

428
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:54.248
Because I'm in love with Flint.

429
00:22:55.124 --> 00:22:57.227
I'm in love with him.

430
00:22:57.251 --> 00:23:00.963
and I wanted to save him and I didn't care
who I hurt in the process.

431
00:23:04.509 --> 00:23:07.112
Well. at least she admits it.

432
00:23:07.136 --> 00:23:09.281
That's right. I admit it.

433
00:23:09.305 --> 00:23:10.783
I'm tired of hiding.

434
00:23:10.807 --> 00:23:12.308
And I'm tired of lying.

435
00:23:13.309 --> 00:23:14.495
You want the rest of it?

436
00:23:14.519 --> 00:23:15.788
Cat. don't.

437
00:23:15.812 --> 00:23:19.690
I did it because I wanted to save Flint
and I wanted to kill you.

438
00:23:20.733 --> 00:23:22.086
Desperately.

439
00:23:22.110 --> 00:23:24.296
So. you were the one who hired Addison.

440
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:25.839
Yes.

441
00:23:25.863 --> 00:23:28.258
You're the one who told the mayor
about my booze delivery.

442
00:23:28.282 --> 00:23:29.718
Yes.

443
00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:31.762
- You're my Judas.
- That's right.

444
00:23:31.786 --> 00:23:33.430
So go ahead and kill me.

445
00:23:33.454 --> 00:23:36.183
But do it because you want me dead.

446
00:23:36.207 --> 00:23:38.894
not because you think
it'll prove something about Ben.

447
00:23:38.918 --> 00:23:41.271
The only thing he's guilty of

448
00:23:41.295 --> 00:23:43.047
is being in way over his head.

449
00:23:45.341 --> 00:23:47.361
You see. Reilly?

450
00:23:47.385 --> 00:23:51.139
That's the difference between convinced...

451
00:23:51.848 --> 00:23:52.866
and certain.

452
00:23:52.890 --> 00:23:54.201
No - Whoa. whoa. whoa.

453
00:23:54.225 --> 00:23:56.268
Whoa. whoa!

454
00:23:58.813 --> 00:24:00.791
Did I come at a bad time?

455
00:24:00.815 --> 00:24:02.000
Not at all.

456
00:24:02.024 --> 00:24:03.961
Silvermane was just teaching us a lesson

457
00:24:03.985 --> 00:24:06.296
about how to kill a defenseless woman.

458
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:07.548
Sorry about that.

459
00:24:07.572 --> 00:24:08.781
Go to hell.

460
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:13.679
Well. isn't this a pleasant surprise?

461
00:24:13.703 --> 00:24:16.181
That's close enough for my taste.

462
00:24:16.205 --> 00:24:17.933
- How's it going. Reilly?
- Peachy.

463
00:24:17.957 --> 00:24:20.144
Look.
you wanted me to come. so I came.

464
00:24:20.168 --> 00:24:21.353
What do you want?

465
00:24:21.377 --> 00:24:22.813
I like that.

466
00:24:22.837 --> 00:24:24.773
Straight and to the point.

467
00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:26.150
Let's talk business.

468
00:24:26.174 --> 00:24:27.317
Yeah. let's.

469
00:24:27.341 --> 00:24:29.278
I don't believe for a second

470
00:24:29.302 --> 00:24:31.238
that you're working for the mayor.

471
00:24:31.262 --> 00:24:33.973
You're too bright and he's too dumb.

472
00:24:34.974 --> 00:24:37.018
So why don't you come work for me?

473
00:24:38.102 --> 00:24:39.937
You can't beat us. Why not join us?

474
00:24:40.855 --> 00:24:42.916
Who says I can't beat you?

475
00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:43.941
Me. for one.

476
00:24:44.859 --> 00:24:46.128
I'll second that.

477
00:24:46.152 --> 00:24:47.546
I'm sorry.

478
00:24:47.570 --> 00:24:50.257
are you forgetting that I'm The Spider?

479
00:24:50.281 --> 00:24:51.717
And I can kick both your asses?

480
00:24:51.741 --> 00:24:53.969
Actually. not to overstep.

481
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:56.871
but I suggest you hear Mr. Byrne out.

482
00:24:57.705 --> 00:25:00.517
I-I'm sorry.
you want me to listen to Silvermane?

483
00:25:00.541 --> 00:25:03.145
I'm merely saying. if we're being honest.

484
00:25:03.169 --> 00:25:05.630
you're not as young as you once were.

485
00:25:06.923 --> 00:25:08.775
I'm actually in great shape.

486
00:25:08.799 --> 00:25:10.360
Yeah. Fit as a fiddle.

487
00:25:10.384 --> 00:25:12.571
- Downright spry.
- I'm merely suggesting

488
00:25:12.595 --> 00:25:16.950
you might not want to leap headlong
into confrontation

489
00:25:16.974 --> 00:25:20.228
so soon after your big battle
with Lonnie Lincoln.

490
00:25:22.355 --> 00:25:23.916
Yeah. You might want to take a break.

491
00:25:23.940 --> 00:25:25.483
You know. rest up.

492
00:25:26.484 --> 00:25:27.920
Right.

493
00:25:27.944 --> 00:25:29.755
So. why don't you give him the antidote

494
00:25:29.779 --> 00:25:31.757
and you give me my two G's
and we can all be on

495
00:25:31.781 --> 00:25:33.634
- our merry ways?
- Yeah.

496
00:25:33.658 --> 00:25:36.011
My. my.

497
00:25:36.035 --> 00:25:38.722
How interesting.

498
00:25:38.746 --> 00:25:41.725
So many plotlines to follow.

499
00:25:41.749 --> 00:25:43.876
How about we add one more?

500
00:25:44.877 --> 00:25:46.897
Found her skulking around outside.

501
00:25:46.921 --> 00:25:49.422
- I'm so sorry. Ben. I shouldn't have.
- Quiet. lady.

502
00:25:50.925 --> 00:25:53.094
And look what she had on her. boss.

503
00:25:58.057 --> 00:26:00.535
W-What? You-you wanted me
to just bring the stuff in here?

504
00:26:00.559 --> 00:26:01.620
Seemed dumb.

505
00:26:01.644 --> 00:26:04.646
You're right. this is much better.

506
00:26:10.152 --> 00:26:14.174
So. this is what the fuss is all about?

507
00:26:14.198 --> 00:26:15.300
Bring it here.

508
00:26:15.324 --> 00:26:17.659
Yeah. yeah. just give me one second there.

509
00:26:20.288 --> 00:26:22.290
How's that feel?

510
00:26:23.749 --> 00:26:25.126
Why the hell did you do that?

511
00:26:26.168 --> 00:26:27.837
Just wanted to see if it worked.

512
00:26:31.465 --> 00:26:33.235
Yep. Seems like it does.

513
00:26:33.259 --> 00:26:34.611
Give it here. buddy.

514
00:26:34.635 --> 00:26:35.654
What. these?

515
00:26:35.678 --> 00:26:37.554
Yeah. No games.

516
00:26:38.764 --> 00:26:42.494
But what if I want to play a game?

517
00:26:42.518 --> 00:26:45.872
And let's call it "Why Should I?"

518
00:26:45.896 --> 00:26:48.858
I'm not in the business
of explaining myself.

519
00:26:49.859 --> 00:26:52.754
Not to you. not to anybody.

520
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:54.298
Now hand it over.

521
00:26:54.322 --> 00:26:55.966
The Spider's no threat now.

522
00:26:55.990 --> 00:26:58.552
So. I'm wondering.

523
00:26:58.576 --> 00:27:00.762
why is it that you're so keen

524
00:27:00.786 --> 00:27:03.390
on having whatever's in these syringes?

525
00:27:03.414 --> 00:27:05.934
You see. I think

526
00:27:05.958 --> 00:27:08.812
it's because you want to control us.

527
00:27:08.836 --> 00:27:12.399
You want to have power over us.

528
00:27:12.423 --> 00:27:15.402
Flint. take care of this guy for me.

529
00:27:15.426 --> 00:27:18.447
Otherwise. why don't I just smash
these last two vials.

530
00:27:18.471 --> 00:27:20.782
and we'll just call it a day?

531
00:27:20.806 --> 00:27:22.659
Flint. you're still with me. son.

532
00:27:22.683 --> 00:27:24.101
You both are.

533
00:27:25.353 --> 00:27:27.938
You know I would never
touch a hair on her head.

534
00:27:28.522 --> 00:27:30.334
You know what to do.

535
00:27:30.358 --> 00:27:31.626
Does he?

536
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:35.672
Now. his girlfriend. she knew what to do.

537
00:27:35.696 --> 00:27:40.326
You just didn't have the balls.

538
00:27:41.327 --> 00:27:42.328
Careful.

539
00:27:43.329 --> 00:27:44.931
He's not your friend. Flint.

540
00:27:44.955 --> 00:27:46.957
He's not even your boss.

541
00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:52.147
He's your puppet master.

542
00:27:52.171 --> 00:27:53.774
Pulling on your strings

543
00:27:53.798 --> 00:27:56.341
and making you dance.

544
00:27:58.886 --> 00:28:00.364
But why let him?

545
00:28:00.388 --> 00:28:01.948
Look at him.

546
00:28:01.972 --> 00:28:03.766
He's not special.

547
00:28:05.476 --> 00:28:09.998
He's just an old man in an expensive suit.

548
00:28:10.022 --> 00:28:12.209
fighting to stay relevant.

549
00:28:12.233 --> 00:28:15.045
Consider your words carefully. my boy.

550
00:28:15.069 --> 00:28:16.903
They may be your last.

551
00:28:21.283 --> 00:28:22.761
Now...

552
00:28:22.785 --> 00:28:24.954
let's see who's behind the mask.

553
00:28:37.299 --> 00:28:38.443
What the hell?

554
00:28:38.467 --> 00:28:39.552
The reporter?

555
00:28:49.520 --> 00:28:50.521
Holy sh.

556
00:29:02.283 --> 00:29:03.885
Robbie? Come on.

557
00:29:03.909 --> 00:29:05.327
<i>Hijo de tu madre.</i>

558
00:29:15.337 --> 00:29:16.755
Duck!

559
00:29:32.146 --> 00:29:33.898
Ben. behind you!

560
00:29:40.988 --> 00:29:42.924
- Ben.
- Robbie.

561
00:29:42.948 --> 00:29:44.551
Robbie. Is he okay?

562
00:29:44.575 --> 00:29:46.636
Yeah. I think so.

563
00:29:46.660 --> 00:29:49.413
I get why you don't like this job.

564
00:30:03.511 --> 00:30:04.905
Hi. fellas.

565
00:30:04.929 --> 00:30:06.096
Can I get you a drink?

566
00:30:47.596 --> 00:30:49.356
- Is that The Spider?
- What's going on here?

567
00:30:53.894 --> 00:30:55.479
Lookie. lookie.

568
00:31:07.825 --> 00:31:10.035
All right. Here goes nothing.

569
00:31:14.873 --> 00:31:16.584
Come and get it.

570
00:31:36.478 --> 00:31:37.605
No.

571
00:32:34.286 --> 00:32:35.704
What happened?

572
00:32:55.516 --> 00:32:56.826
After all I did for you.

573
00:32:56.850 --> 00:32:59.913
it breaks my heart
that you'd betray me like that.

574
00:32:59.937 --> 00:33:02.772
No. it breaks your heart
that you didn't see it was me.

575
00:33:04.525 --> 00:33:06.127
Is this because of that dentist?

576
00:33:06.151 --> 00:33:08.254
You'd have never have been happy with him.

577
00:33:08.278 --> 00:33:11.841
filling cavities
in some New Jersey suburb.

578
00:33:11.865 --> 00:33:13.741
I saved your life when I got rid of him.

579
00:33:15.202 --> 00:33:17.806
First the dentist. then Flint.

580
00:33:17.830 --> 00:33:20.225
You sure can pick them. can't you?

581
00:33:20.249 --> 00:33:23.186
That's right. I can pick my men.

582
00:33:23.210 --> 00:33:24.813
I can pick my dresses

583
00:33:24.837 --> 00:33:26.295
and I can pick my songs.

584
00:33:29.883 --> 00:33:32.445
Liar. You loved being kept.

585
00:33:32.469 --> 00:33:34.322
You loved being cared for.

586
00:33:34.346 --> 00:33:36.074
Fed. dressed.

587
00:33:36.098 --> 00:33:38.535
Painted head to toe.

588
00:33:38.559 --> 00:33:40.328
Not a hair out of place.

589
00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:43.248
Not a care in the world
but that perch on the stage.

590
00:33:43.272 --> 00:33:45.524
The focus of all admiration.

591
00:33:46.859 --> 00:33:49.713
Never be satisfied. Is that what you said?

592
00:33:49.737 --> 00:33:52.364
Don't accept what's given to you.

593
00:34:00.164 --> 00:34:02.600
My one regret...

594
00:34:02.624 --> 00:34:04.877
is I only get to kill you once.

595
00:34:15.429 --> 00:34:17.263
The truth is. my love...

596
00:34:18.932 --> 00:34:20.350
I'm happy it's you.

597
00:34:53.634 --> 00:34:55.570
Come on!

598
00:34:55.594 --> 00:34:58.656
You know. I suppose I should thank you.

599
00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:01.034
For saving your life back in France?

600
00:35:01.058 --> 00:35:02.911
If we're being honest...

601
00:35:02.935 --> 00:35:04.704
I have regrets.

602
00:35:04.728 --> 00:35:06.748
No. no. no. no.

603
00:35:06.772 --> 00:35:10.234
{\an8}For giving me the one thing
I always wanted.

604
00:35:11.235 --> 00:35:13.379
Look at me now. Ma!

605
00:35:13.403 --> 00:35:14.822
I'm a star!

606
00:35:15.447 --> 00:35:16.800
You're not a star.

607
00:35:16.824 --> 00:35:17.884
But you are sick.

608
00:35:17.908 --> 00:35:20.887
And the stronger your power becomes.
the sicker you get.

609
00:35:20.911 --> 00:35:22.639
But I can help you.

610
00:35:22.663 --> 00:35:24.474
No. thanks. pal.

611
00:35:24.498 --> 00:35:26.708
Save your cure for the saps.

612
00:35:33.215 --> 00:35:35.383
Is he all right?

613
00:35:37.052 --> 00:35:38.720
Behind you!

614
00:35:43.225 --> 00:35:44.518
That's not good.

615
00:36:04.621 --> 00:36:06.999
"The Spider."

616
00:36:09.334 --> 00:36:12.004
Looks more like a dog to me.

617
00:36:14.464 --> 00:36:17.174
A bastard cur. at that.

618
00:36:19.511 --> 00:36:21.513
Hey. Look at him squirm.

619
00:36:22.431 --> 00:36:24.807
Some hero you turned out to be.

620
00:36:26.894 --> 00:36:29.622
- I think you proved your point.
- You kidding me?

621
00:36:29.646 --> 00:36:31.624
I've waited my whole life for this.

622
00:36:31.648 --> 00:36:34.294
My star turn on Broadway.

623
00:36:34.318 --> 00:36:36.254
A sold-out show.

624
00:36:36.278 --> 00:36:39.465
Packed house. standing room only.

625
00:36:39.489 --> 00:36:42.159
Boo yourself.

626
00:36:44.036 --> 00:36:46.788
Say goodbye to The Spider. everyone.

627
00:36:55.088 --> 00:36:56.506
Stop!

628
00:36:59.676 --> 00:37:01.404
Honey.

629
00:37:01.428 --> 00:37:04.931
I don't believe for one second
you're gonna pull that trigger.

630
00:37:08.602 --> 00:37:10.145
What a shame.

631
00:37:11.521 --> 00:37:13.230
No!

632
00:37:21.949 --> 00:37:25.219
Aww. Well. well. well.

633
00:37:25.243 --> 00:37:27.972
Ladies and gentlemen. you are in luck.

634
00:37:27.996 --> 00:37:31.059
Tonight will be a double bill.

635
00:37:31.083 --> 00:37:35.313
Featuring me. your leading man Megawatt.

636
00:37:35.337 --> 00:37:39.341
versus the Sandman.

637
00:37:42.469 --> 00:37:44.972
No. I don't think
he likes his new nickname.

638
00:37:45.639 --> 00:37:46.639
Aww.

639
00:37:50.102 --> 00:37:54.082
It seems like our show
has reached its final act.

640
00:37:54.106 --> 00:37:55.815
The denouement.

641
00:38:03.198 --> 00:38:05.259
Good night. sweet prince.

642
00:38:05.283 --> 00:38:10.205
And flights of angels
sing thee to thy rest.

643
00:38:41.570 --> 00:38:43.071
Well done. Spider.

644
00:39:09.264 --> 00:39:11.266
I still have one left.

645
00:39:17.856 --> 00:39:19.042
Why?

646
00:39:19.066 --> 00:39:20.901
You know why.

647
00:39:23.403 --> 00:39:25.030
So does he.

648
00:39:39.878 --> 00:39:41.606
- Spider!
- You look great.

649
00:39:41.630 --> 00:39:43.350
- Thank you. Spider.
- Really appreciate it.

650
00:40:02.359 --> 00:40:04.194
Rest in peace.

651
00:40:23.255 --> 00:40:24.714
You're looking well.

652
00:40:25.715 --> 00:40:27.217
Thanks to you.

653
00:40:29.219 --> 00:40:31.322
Can we have a moment?

654
00:40:31.346 --> 00:40:32.681
Yeah.

655
00:40:37.686 --> 00:40:39.956
I love Flint.

656
00:40:39.980 --> 00:40:42.524
But in a different world.
I really would have run away with you.

657
00:40:44.734 --> 00:40:46.820
You know that. right?

658
00:40:47.445 --> 00:40:49.197
It's one thing to use a guy.

659
00:40:50.532 --> 00:40:53.010
It's another to try
and keep him on the hook

660
00:40:53.034 --> 00:40:55.453
after you've set sail for shore.

661
00:40:56.538 --> 00:40:57.723
Go to hell. Ben.

662
00:40:57.747 --> 00:40:59.225
I have.

663
00:40:59.249 --> 00:41:00.750
I'm keeping it warm for you.

664
00:41:27.777 --> 00:41:29.463
<i>Thank you!</i>

665
00:41:29.487 --> 00:41:31.048
Thank you. New York.

666
00:41:31.072 --> 00:41:33.426
Proud to be your mayor!

667
00:41:33.450 --> 00:41:35.303
You believed in me. and...

668
00:41:35.327 --> 00:41:39.497
You know. I still don't know
if he's a Republican or a Democrat.

669
00:41:40.081 --> 00:41:42.143
Well. what'd it say on the little box
when you voted for him?

670
00:41:42.167 --> 00:41:44.628
I put the X where it said. "Vote for crap."

671
00:41:47.923 --> 00:41:49.233
You see that?

672
00:41:49.257 --> 00:41:51.986
You see how it wobbles.
Let's have it not do that.

673
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.530
You heard the lady. No wobblin'.

674
00:41:54.554 --> 00:41:57.682
How's a guy supposed to do
his geometricals on a wobbly desk?

675
00:41:59.184 --> 00:42:01.746
Well. back to the salt mines.

676
00:42:01.770 --> 00:42:03.664
So. after all that.

677
00:42:03.688 --> 00:42:05.625
I get a newspaper to run.

678
00:42:05.649 --> 00:42:07.501
Morris wins. Flint gets the girl

679
00:42:07.525 --> 00:42:09.921
and Janet gets a new office.

680
00:42:09.945 --> 00:42:11.154
What do you get?

681
00:42:12.989 --> 00:42:14.824
A new lease on life?

682
00:42:15.784 --> 00:42:20.496
I'll just settle for a really good hot dog.

683
00:42:21.665 --> 00:42:24.334
The paperweight lives.

684
00:42:28.380 --> 00:42:30.173
Reilly Ruiz Investigations.

685
00:42:32.259 --> 00:42:34.969
Absolutely. we're open.
I can slot you in at...

686
00:42:36.763 --> 00:42:39.683
You know what? You're in luck.
we just had a cancellation for 2:00 p.m.

687
00:42:40.558 --> 00:42:42.078
Great.

688
00:42:42.102 --> 00:42:43.788
See you then.

689
00:42:43.812 --> 00:42:44.997
Why 2:00?

690
00:42:45.021 --> 00:42:46.874
Makes us seem busy.

691
00:42:46.898 --> 00:42:49.627
Also. I want that hot dog.

692
00:42:49.651 --> 00:42:51.504
Robbie's buying.

693
00:42:51.528 --> 00:42:53.839
What? You run your own newspaper now.

694
00:42:53.863 --> 00:42:55.739
Yeah. and it pays worse than the <i>Bugle.</i>

695
00:42:59.327 --> 00:43:01.620
Come on. Robertson.
You don't want to buy me a hot dog?
